{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772130404,"nonce":"Zo0/Z97Wom5dbF8e0Jzb6tph/dY=","title":"Feedbax Studio: cloud training orchestration + CDE graph editing","message":"## Summary\n\nAdd cloud training orchestration to Feedbax Studio and make CDE controllers editable as causal subgraphs in the graph editor.\n\n## Motivation\n\nCurrently Studio is fully local with a stub training backend. We need:\n1. Remote training on cloud GPUs/TPUs with live monitoring (loss curves, logs, trajectory snapshots)\n2. Preemption-safe data sync (spot instances get killed without warning)\n3. CDE controller models representable and editable in the graph canvas\n4. Interactive mid-training simulation with streamed intermediate weights\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n### CDE as Editable Causal Subgraph\n\nCDE controllers are editable subgraphs (NOT black boxes). The CDE step is a directed acyclic graph within a single timestep — different variants (standard CDE, +decay, +Anti-NF gate, INCDE, GRU-ODE) are different wirings of existing primitives (MLP, GRU, Linear, Sum, Scale, MatMul, Subtract, Sigmoid). Provide preset templates for known architectures; users can customize wiring.\n\nSubgraph contract: input ports (obs, obs_prev, h_prev) → output ports (h_new, action). Recurrence via existing state-flow edges.\n\n### Dynamical System Taxonomy\n\n| Type | Editing | Examples |\n|---|---|---|\n| Causal subgraph | Editable wiring | CDE controller, neural architectures |\n| DAE subgraph | Equation editor | Musculoskeletal plant |\n| Atomic component | Properties panel | MLP, GRU, Linear, Gain |\n\nAll share Component execution contract. Unification at execution level, not editing level.\n\n### Protocol: gRPC over Tailscale\n\ngRPC with server-side streaming for structured multi-stream data. REST for CRUD. Tailscale mesh for NAT-traversing connectivity. Cloudflare Tunnel fallback.\n\nRPCs: StartRun, StopRun, StreamMetrics, StreamLogs, StreamTrajectories, StreamCheckpoints (pull-on-demand), PushControl (pause/resume/set_lr), Heartbeat.\n\nReconnection via monotonic sequence numbers per stream. Append-only event log format.\n\n### Remote Data Flow\n\n```\nRemote Worker                     Studio (local)\n─────────────                     ──────────────\nmetrics stream ──────────────→  Live loss curves (Training tab)\nlog stream ──────────────────→  Console tab (new bottom-shelf tab)\ntrajectory snapshots (periodic)→  3D Trajectory viewer (existing)\nweight checkpoints (on demand) → Local simulation / inspect\nheartbeat ───────────────────→  Status bar indicator\n```\n\n## Phases\n\n1. **Local streaming refactor**: Real training backend, structured streaming, live loss chart, console tab\n2. **Headless worker mode (local)**: Training as separate process, new protocol, decoupled from Studio backend\n3. **Tailscale remote worker**: Manual remote setup, Tailscale IP, live metrics/logs\n4. **Artifact streaming**: Trajectory snapshots + checkpoint pull. Mid-training local simulation\n5. **CDE graph editing**: CDE as editable subgraph with architecture templates (parallel to 1-4)\n6. **Orchestration**: Automated instance creation, auth, run lifecycle\n\n## Deep Context\n\nA detailed context dump with full architectural exploration, Codex analysis, experiment history, and file locations is available at:\n\n`~/.claude/projects/-Users-mll-Main-10-Projects-10-PhD-20-Feedbax-feedbax/memory/studio-cloud-training-context.md`\n\nLoad this file before starting implementation work.\n\n## Prior Art\n\nAdopt patterns from: W\u0026B (control/data plane separation, async buffered logging), TensorBoard (append-only event logs), MLflow (named artifacts with explicit fetch). Avoid: polling-only UIs, training loop blocking on UI.","files":null}]}